title: Independent candidate Asfand Yar Khan Kakar wins PB-47
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Asfand Yar Khan Kakar won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-47, Pishin-I by securing 21,714 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ullema-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI) candidate Kamal Uddin who bagged 18,989 votes.
Voters turn-out remained at 51.64 per cent.
